snippet.textDisplay:
Hello, this is for those that are in a hurry but still wanna watch some parts untill they come home or they can't watch it fully or want to watch it but they are kind of person that doesn't end up sitting trought the entire thing,because of their short attention span or big creative mind and wonder to other educational things fast.

I watched this 3 times and it's really a deep and wise conversation, learned a lot from these guys, I recommend everyone to watch it at least 2 times to get everything sink in, the fact that I am making those time stamps is because I was gonna decide to watch it for the third time anyways and just opened a notepad on my 2nd monitor and decided it would be a cool thing if this appeared in comments and help someone find something they want or skip to the things they wanted to know at the time.

I recommend watching this while not skipping fully trought the timestamps, because you are gonna learn a lot more if you watch as much as you can, but if you are a person thats in a hurry do it faster, everyone can take this as they want, i hope it helps! <:

0:30 - Start (after intro)

1:00 - Em shows Mike his appreaciation for being a huge fan

1:45 - Mike asks Em ''Why did you become who you were? ''

3:56 - Em explains how he got into Hip Hop and Rap

13:25 - Em shows Mike his appreaciation again for his boxing career

15:43 - Em explains his Boxing basics from the past

17:21 - Important life message by Mike

17:56 - Funny

19:14 - How to be a fighter in life, in anything

21:14 - Mike shares his wisdom

23:49 - Mike tells Em his appreaciation for being a huge fan

24:53 - Em about hunger and money within any success

25:35 - Mike talks about his life before and movie Hungover

29:17 - Em and Mike share what makes person feel they aren't good enough

31:06 - Changing topic about Oscars ._. (I personally didn't like this, but that's me)

32:45 - Mike asks Em about his daughter Hailie and raising kids

34:22 - Crew thanks Em for coming on the Show

35:31 - Em shares story of Denaun and him

36:53 - Conversation about Costantino D'Amato (Cus)

39:42 - Quote from Mike that really caught my attention

'' If you are not crazy in this crazy world, I really feel sorry for you''

40:00 - How do we find our purpose in life












Such a fun, funny, educational, eye opening and chilled podcast.

snippet.textDisplay:
Mike, be the wiseman.. life is short and some day soon you'll be a grandfather..

An old Cherokee is teaching his grandson about life. “A fight is going on inside me,” he said to the boy. “It is a terrible fight and it is between two wolves. One is evil – he is anger, envy, sorrow, regret, greed, arrogance, self-pity, guilt, resentment, inferiority, lies, false pride, superiority, and ego.”

 He continued, “The other is good – he is joy, peace, love, hope, serenity, humility, kindness, benevolence, empathy, generosity, truth, compassion, and faith. The same fight is going on inside you – and inside every other person, too.”

 The grandson thought about it for a minute and then asked his grandfather, “Which wolf will win?”

 The old Cherokee simply replied, “The one you feed.”
